issues.shortMessage: There's no need to call "ToString()", the compiler will do it for you.
issues.fullMessage: Invoking a method designed to return a string representation of an object which is already a string is a waste of keystrokes. Similarly, explicitly invoking "ToString()" when the compiler would do it implicitly is also needless code-bloat.
